3:30 PM Defendant Devin L Kwick in court, in custody.  Attorney Jerome J Babiak in court for Devin L Kwick.  Attorney Nathan T. Oswald in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Officer Borchardt is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being dispatched to a residence for a disturbance that had occurred between the defendant and his girlfriend. Defendant left the residence by the time he arrived. Testifies to making contact w/ the defendant. Witness identifies the defendant in court, court recognizes. Testifies to observing injuries on the defendant. Testifies to the statement made by the defendant regarding the incident that happened. Testifies to Officer Ament informing him there was probable cause. Testifies to defendant making a fist and punch forward towards the officer. Testifies to the defendant being taken into custody and taken to the Marshfield Medical Center. Testifies to reviewing Officer Endries report from when he was at the Marshfield Medical Center with the defendant. Testifies to the nurse stating the defendants robe got stuck in the wheel chair and the nurse tried helping the defendant and the defendant kicked or pushed the wheel chair at her and struck her knee. 

Court finds probable cause to believe a felony was committed and the defendant committed it.

Attorney Babiak requests a Competency Exam for the defendant, Court grants.

Bond is continued.
Arraignment scheduled for May 17, 2022 at 10:00 am.
